Acquired causes of pure red cell aplasia are all except NSAIDs. PRCA happens in cases of major ABO-mismatch between donor and recipient and is thought to be due to inhibition of donor erythroid progenitors by residual host isohemagglutinins Pure red cell hypoplasia with deletion of the long arm of a chromosome 5(5g-) is seen where the bone marrow represents lowered erythroid cells with normal granulocytic and megakaryocytic precursors. LEukemia and Lymphoma can present with PRCA. Most common Cause of PRCA is Parvovirus Drugs like:Phenytoin, azathioprine, Chloramphenicol,Procainamide and isoniazid can cause pure red cell aplasia.<br />
&nbsp;
